cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper discusses spectrum access in cognitive radios, which involves communication and networking aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the impact of erroneous detection of spectrum holes on the capacity of the secondary channel, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper proposes cooperative communication models, which involve collaboration between multiple cognitive transmitters and receivers, and this falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the impact of imperfect information exchange on the capacity and achievable throughput, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper proposes protocols that can be extended to multiuser secondary networks, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
